title: Kuwait Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Kuwait Three Month Interbank Rate was at 1.56 percent on Monday November 7. Interbank Rate in Kuwait averaged 4.48 percent from 1983 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 11.95 percent in June of 1984 and a record low of 0.63 percent in February of 2013. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - Kuwait Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Central Bank of Kuwait
